Rear Admiral Douglas Fears has been appointed as a Deputy Assistant to the President and Homeland Security and Counterterrorism Advisor on the National Security Council staff. He brings over three decades of experience in counterterrorism, cybersecurity, and disaster response. Fears will oversee the NSC Cybersecurity Directorate and coordinate interagency efforts during disaster response. He is an alumnus of the U.S. Coast Guard Academy, the U.S. Naval War College, and Harvard University.